commentary: Shahid Afridi to Ingram, no run Afridi reviews this. He has not even waited to consult with the captain. That looked really really close to me. Tossed up, slow through the air, beat Ingram's sweep, and hit him low on the pad. No edge on it. So let's see where it pitched and where it was headed. It is taking them an age to process this. Just get on with it. They are still debating whether there is an edge on it. A thousand replays with Hot Spot, and we are still not convinced. Just move on, people. They are looking for a touch on the top strap of the glove. A front-on replay doesn't quite show that touch, but there is a slight Hot Spot on that glove strap as the ball passes. So they don't even look at where the ball pitched and where it was headed because he is deemed to have played this
shortText: Shahid Afridi to Ingram, no run
text: Afridi reviews this. He has not even waited to consult with the captain. That looked really really close to me. Tossed up, slow through the air, beat Ingram's sweep, and hit him low on the pad. No edge on it. So let's see where it pitched and where it was headed. It is taking them an age to process this. Just get on with it. They are still debating whether there is an edge on it. A thousand replays with Hot Spot, and we are still not convinced. Just move on, people. They are looking for a touch on the top strap of the glove. A front-on replay doesn't quite show that touch, but there is a slight Hot Spot on that glove strap as the ball passes. So they don't even look at where the ball pitched and where it was headed because he is deemed to have played this

commentary: Peterson to Younis Khan, no run turns away from Younis, who pushes forward, and de Villiers and Peterson go up for the catch spontaneously. Umpire says not out, so South Africa will review it. He has missed this by a mile, and it's the bat hitting the pad that has created the noise. We stay with not-out. It was superb from Younis: he seems to have told AB if he thought this was edged, why doesn't he back himself up and go for the review

commentary: Kleinveldt to Younis Khan, OUT High drama. Kleinveldt is enjoying great luck here. Driven hard back at Kleinveldt, he has got a touch on this, and Hafeez is caught well short while backing up. There is a clear deflection as the ball passes his outstretched hand. Kleinveldt is not pleased that nobody has run after the ricochet, and the Pakistan batsmen are running. 'What if he is in?' he seems to be telling his mates. It doesn't matter Rory. Hafeez is well short. Although we have had many replays, and I have no doubt the ball hit the ring finger of Kleinveldt's hand. I think Billy Bowden is not sure beyond all reasonable doubt. And we have waited for about five minutes already. Finally he has been given out. I know people will say it is a horribly unlucky way to get out, but I don't agree: you leave your crease at your own peril
shortText: Kleinveldt to Younis Khan, OUT
text: High drama. Kleinveldt is enjoying great luck here. Driven hard back at Kleinveldt, he has got a touch on this, and Hafeez is caught well short while backing up. There is a clear deflection as the ball passes his outstretched hand. Kleinveldt is not pleased that nobody has run after the ricochet, and the Pakistan batsmen are running. 'What if he is in?' he seems to be telling his mates. It doesn't matter Rory. Hafeez is well short. Although we have had many replays, and I have no doubt the ball hit the ring finger of Kleinveldt's hand. I think Billy Bowden is not sure beyond all reasonable doubt. And we have waited for about five minutes already. Finally he has been given out. I know people will say it is a horribly unlucky way to get out, but I don't agree: you leave your crease at your own peril

commentary: Kleinveldt to Saeed Ajmal, OUT Kleinveldt is on a hat-trick, and I am surprised why they aren't reviewing this one. They can't take that one home, may as well use it up. This is not plumb. Length ball, seaming in, seemingly past the inside edge, but has this hit him outside the line of off? First of all, there was a huge inside edge on this one. I really wonder why they didn't review this
